				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Drum of the Beast worth 25k?<a name="9014"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 10 03 1:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>They are one of 3 drops off an ULTRA RARE mob in Siren's Grotto but a mob that is easily one group killable.  Some camps for this take over 3 days of killing to get the mob to even spawn once much less drop the Drums out of the possible drops.  Take into account that if someone dies here, the CR is h*ll and getting a cleric to come rezz someone is a severe pain in the a$.  That is why they are so expensive to buy.  They have a 2.6 modifyer vice the 2.3 on the Walrus Skin Drums and the 2.4 on the Selos Drums of the March and, being primary only, can be help at the same time as the Bard Epic so you have a h*ll of a lot better stats and resists as well as it giving a nice boost to the Resist songs and Chants as well.  Every bit helps.  Look at the current bard song spreadsheet to see how much better they are.  24kpp is a good price to pay for the Drums as far as the Seventh Hammer is concerned.  I have never seen them sell for less.  Until you can get into BoT and get the Thunderous Drums of Karana, these are the best drums you will ever use.  They also have long duration instant cast EB on them and can be given to a level 1 bard all of which makes them a Super Uber set of drums.</span></td>
