				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Drum of the Beast worth 25k?<a name="9211"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 16 03 1:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hey all, first time posting to this site but have been a reader for a long while.  Just figured I'd post that I usually see the greedy people selling them for 40k on Quellious.  I sold two for 15k.  Just did a WTS DoTB and asked for an offer.  Both times i was offered 15k so I'm guessing that's about the going price for them on Quellios for the most part.
<br />

<br />
As far as the camp goes.  The mob's not ultra rare by any means.  I personally use the zone to get my cleric some exp while killing the wateries and icy's.  Best area I found to do it is at that siren castle.  Invis through the castle with a healer and go up the ramp between the two sirens and the bulthar.  Pass the two icy / wateries and camp the corner on the next level down.  You're between a set of three mobs and 2 mobs you passed.  Kill the 2, kill the three, then invis and go back into siren's castle, make a right and head down to bottom near the waterhole.  Fight the two down there, then fight the two you passed when entering this section by the builthar on that side.  Total of 9 mobs.  Each time I've killed them all, the shimmering has spawned on next set of respawns.  Up to 6 DotB from just doing this.  I'm usually just giving the dotb to bard friends.  Have one more DoTB to give away as of last night since I got Thunderous Drums of Karana.  Nice to see those dropping nowadays<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Another camp btw is by giong down the well and then up into that underwater siren's section.  There's 6 icy / wateries here.  If you have your 64 charm you can harmony and charm the wateries or icies and throw them into the mermaid pool.  Let the mermaids kill them off since they won't come out of the water if charm breaks.  Then recharm and throw mob back in the pool.  I'm sure this has been posted before though.
<br />

<br />
- Meilos</span></td>
